{\rtf1\ansi\deff0\fs22---\linetitle: "Archive Policy v1 — GILC & Digital Fabrica"\lineclassification: Governance+Ethics+StrategicDesign\linevalidators:\line\bullet	ab role: "Ethics Steward"\line\bullet	ab role: "Data Steward"\line\bullet	ab role: "Executive Secretary"\linelicense: Public-Licensed / CodexLinked\linetags: [policy, archive, taxonomy, retention, access, governance]\linelinks:\line\bullet	ab stitchia-protocol-dev/docs/GILC_Fabrica_Blueprint.md\line\bullet	ab stitchia-protocol-dev/scrolls/executive_secretary_charter.md\line\bullet	ab vault/documents/onboarding_delyan_donovski.md\line---\line\line\b\fs32 Archive Policy v1 — GILC & Digital Fabrica\b0\fs22\line\linePurpose\line-------\lineEstablish a unified policy for document ingestion, classification, retention, access control, and discovery across GILC and Digital Fabrica.\line\lineScope\line-----\lineApplies to all institutional documents: governance, research, finance, legal, communications, and people operations.\line\lineTaxonomy (Document Types)\line-------------------------\line\bullet	ab Governance: agendas, minutes, resolutions, charters, policies\line\bullet	ab Research: papers, datasets, methods, literature reviews\line\bullet	ab Finance: invoices, receipts, grants, budgets, attestations\line\bullet	ab Legal/IP: contracts, licenses, terms, permissions\line\bullet	ab Communications: announcements, public notices, blog posts\line\bullet	ab People: onboarding, role charters, performance plans\line\lineNaming & Paths\line--------------\line\bullet	ab File name: `<domain>-<YYYY>-<MM>-<DD>-<slug>.md`\line\bullet	ab Suggested folders: `vault/documents/\{governance|research|finance|legal|comms|people|programs|assets\}`\line\bullet	ab IDs: include stable registry ID in braid/registry, not filename\line\lineRetention Schedule (Minimum)\line----------------------------\line\bullet	ab Governance minutes/resolutions: permanent\line\bullet	ab Policies/charters: permanent (maintain superseded versions)\line\bullet	ab Finance records (invoices/receipts): 7 years\line\bullet	ab Research datasets: 5 years or per grant/repository policy\line\bullet	ab Legal/IP artifacts: per contract term + 5 years\line\bullet	ab General communications: 2 years\line\lineAccess Levels\line-------------\line\bullet	ab Public: open docs; default license: Public-Licensed / CodexLinked\line\bullet	ab Internal: council + staff; publish summaries publicly when possible\line\bullet	ab Restricted: legal/finance; sealed; require data minimization and need-to-know\line\lineIngestion Workflow\line------------------\line1) Author with frontmatter; include 'validators', 'tags', and 'links'\line2) Run './quantum process <file>'; confirm 'ethics_status'\line3) Request seals ('./quantum seal') from Ethics Steward + Executive Secretary\line4) Ensure braid edges: tags overlap and 'links' to related scrolls\line5) If dashboard-relevant, include a 'dashboard' block\line\lineDiscovery & Indexing\line--------------------\line\bullet	ab Tags are mandatory; prefer domain + program + subject tags\line\bullet	ab Cross-link by filename or 12-char ID in `links`\line\bullet	ab Use `./quantum build` before releases to refresh braids + dashboard data\line\lineCompliance & Privacy\line--------------------\line\bullet	ab Remove PII from public docs; store sensitive content in Restricted scope\line\bullet	ab Ensure license statements align with Legal Kernel\line\lineRoles & Responsibilities\line------------------------\line\bullet	ab Executive Secretary: policy owner; ensures compliance and registry hygiene\line\bullet	ab Data Steward: taxonomy and discovery quality; dashboard sourcing\line\bullet	ab Ethics Steward: ethics review and guardrails\line\lineVersioning\line----------\line\bullet	ab Update this policy via new scroll revisions; link superseded versions in `links`\line\line}